{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4ec2974e-b9a0-4a02-b6ae-a24124c4299f","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory, so here's general guidance on the switch:\n\n### Changes needed for NuGet Trusted Publishing (OIDC)\n\n**1. NuGet.org setup:**\n- Go to **nuget.org → Manage Packages → Trusted Publishers**\n- Add a GitHub Actions publisher policy (owner, repo, branch/environment)\n\n**2. Workflow changes:**\n\n```yaml\n# Add permissions at the job level\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write   # Required for OIDC token\n      contents: read\n\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      # Build & pack your project...\n      - run: dotnet pack -c Release\n\n      # Push — no API key needed\n      - name: Publish to NuGet\n        run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg\n          --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n**Key differences from your current setup:**\n| Before (API key) | After (OIDC) |\n|---|---|\n| `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` in `--api-key` | No `--api-key` flag at all |\n| No special permissions | `id-token: write` permission required |\n| Key rotated manually | Token is ephemeral, scoped automatically |\n\n**3. Remove** the `NUGET_API_KEY` repository secret once verified.\n\nThe OIDC token is automatically exchanged by the NuGet CLI when `id-token: write` is set and the trusted publisher policy matches. No explicit token-fetch step is needed — `dotnet nuget push` handles it transparently.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"85ac37d7-bb9d-4af9-8213-b3cfb2049783","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There are no files in the repository. The user is asking a general question about switching from NuGet API key to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC) in GitHub Actions. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":469,"requestId":"E422:31693D:6A0DC8F:7267F2D:6A03CCD0"},"id":"71461ab5-2a77-4542-bf0c-69a63fad82b2","timestamp":"2026-05-13T00:59:07.637Z","parentId":"ef7d3038-2f5f-4e34-8c94-d38d970cd716"}
